<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="W" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Waken" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Waken,</orth> to rouse from sleep: <bibl n="shak. 3h6 4.3.19" default="NO" valid="yes">H6C IV, 3, 19</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 3.1.28" default="NO" valid="yes">Rom. III, 1, 28</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. rom 4.4.24" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 24</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. oth 2.1.188" default="NO" valid="yes">Oth. II, 1, 188</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. cym 2.2.13" default="NO" valid="yes">Cymb. II, 2, 13</bibl>. Metaphorically: <cit><quote>in your --ed hate,</quote> <bibl n="shak. son 117.12" default="NO" valid="yes">Sonn. 117, 12</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>your sleepy thoughts, which here we w. to our country's good,</quote> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.7.124" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 7, 124</bibl></cit>. <cit><quote>that I might w. reverence,</quote> <bibl n="shak. tro 1.3.227" default="NO" valid="yes">Troil. I, 3, 227</bibl></cit>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>